[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mfor such parent company guarantees . contingent acquisition obligations we have structured certain acquisitions with [0m       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92madditional contingent purchase price obligations in order to reduce the potential risk associated with negative future [0m     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mperformance of the acquired entity . in addition , we have entered into agreements that may require us to purchase [0m         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92madditional equity interests in certain consolidated and unconsolidated subsidiaries . the amounts relating to these [0m        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mtransactions ...[0m                                                                                                            [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mTABLE:[0m                                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mRow Label       [0m[92m2009    [0m[92m2010    [0m[92m2011    [0m[92m2012    [0m[92m2013    [0m[92mthereafter      [0m[92mtotal[0m                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mdeferred acquisition payments   [0m[92m67.5    [0m[92m32.1    [0m[92m30.1    [0m[92m4.5     [0m[92m5.7     [0m[92m2014.0  [0m[92m139.9[0m                                       [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mput and call options with affiliates1   [0m[92m11.8    [0m[92m34.3    [0m[92m73.6    [0m[92m70.8    [0m[92m70.2    [0m[92m2.2     [0m[92m262.9[0m                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mtotal   [0m[92m76.7    [0m[92m65.1    [0m[92m103.0   [0m[92m74.6    [0m[92m75.6    [0m[92m2.2     [0m[92m397.2[0m                                                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mtotal contingent acquisition payments   [0m[92m79.3    [0m[92m66.4    [0m[92m103.7   [0m[92m75.3    [0m[92m75.9    [0m[92m2.2     [0m[92m402.8[0m                               [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mRow Label       [0m[92m2009    [0m[92m2010    [0m[92m2011    [0m[92m2012    [0m[92m2013    [0m[92mthereafter      [0m[92mtotal[0m                                               [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m

[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mANALYSIS STRATEGY:[0m                                                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 1 - UNDERSTAND THE QUESTION:[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What specific metric is being asked for?[0m                                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What time periods are involved?[0m                                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are there conversational references to resolve?[0m                                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- What type of calculation is needed (lookup, change, ratio, percentage)?[0m                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 2 - RESOLVE CONVERSATIONAL CONTEXT:[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- If question contains "that", "it", "this value" â†’ use the most recent result from conversation history[0m                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Example: Previous answer was 78.93, question asks "what is that divided by 100?" â†’ use 78.93[0m                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the previous year" â†’ identify specific year from context[0m                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- "the difference between the two values" â†’ use the two most recently mentioned values[0m                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 3 - DATA EXTRACTION:[0m                                                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Scan the ENTIRE table systematically (all rows, all columns)[0m                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Look for EXACT metric name matches first, then synonyms[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- When you see years (2012, 2014), distinguish:[0m                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Column headers (time periods) vs actual numeric values[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m  * Don't confuse year labels with the data values[0m                                                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- For ambiguous cases, choose the value that makes business sense for the question[0m                                          [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 4 - CALCULATION:[0m                                                                                                       [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Percentage change: (new - old) / old[0m                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Differences: pay attention to order ("change from A to B" = B - A)[0m                                                        [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Ratios: check question for correct numerator/denominator[0m                                                                  [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Preserve negative signs for declines, losses, decreases[0m                                                                   [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mSTEP 5 - VERIFICATION:[0m                                                                                                      [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Does the result magnitude make sense?[0m                                                                                     [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Are signs correct (positive/negative)?[0m                                                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Is the scale appropriate?[0m                                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m                                                                                                                              [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92mCOMMON ERROR PATTERNS TO AVOID:[0m                                                                                             [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't return years (2012, 2014) when asked for financial values[0m                                                           [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't lose negative signs in calculations[0m                                                                                 [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't confuse different metrics (net earnings â‰  operating income)[0m                                                         [35mâ”‚[0m
[35mâ”‚[0m  [92m- Don't ignore conversational context ("that" refers to previous result)[0m                                                    [35mâ”‚[0m
